Equity Membership Classifications
Golf
Equity Golf membership is an equity family membership entitling the Member, spouse or significant other, and all dependent children up to the age of 25 to full use of all Club facilities.
Sports/ Social
The Invitational Sports/ Social membership is a non-equity family membership entitling the Member, spouse or significant other, and all dependent children up to the age of 23 to full use of all tennis, swimming and social facilities of the Club. The Sports/Social package also includes 16 rounds of golf at the rate of a guest. (4 Rounds in Season, 12 Out of Season)
For more information, please contact Brandon Smith at 561-793-1703 ext. 10 or
[email protected]

Mayacoo Team Tennis
Mayacoo Lakes currently has the following Team Tennis groups:
Women's Division 3
Palm Beach County Women's Tennis League. Ladies team practice is held on Tuesdays from 9 - 11, focusing on partner play and team strategy.
Match Days are Thursday, starting at 10 a.m. Matches are held on our home courts or away at participating clubs throughout Palm Beach County.
If you are interested in joining the team, please contact BJ Munroe or Team Captain Alice Randolph (561) 801-1360.
